<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>üî• Unpopular Opinion Generator üî•</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">Defend the indefensible. Argue the unarguable. Prove your point with punctuation!</p>

        <div class="opinion-display" id="opinionDisplay">
            <p class="placeholder">Click below to reveal your unpopular opinion...</p>
        </div>

        <button class="generate-btn" id="generateBtn" onclick="generateOpinion()">
            Generate My Unpopular Opinion
        </button>

        <div class="requirements">
            <h3>üìù Your Mission:</h3>
            <p>‚úçÔ∏è Write approximately 300 words defending (or attacking) this opinion</p>
            <p>üéØ Use advanced punctuation throughout: colons, semicolons, and dashes</p>
            <p>üí™ Make your argument sophisticated and well-reasoned</p>
        </div>

        <div class="instructions">
            <h3>How to Structure Your Writing:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>State your position clearly</strong> ‚Äî do you agree or disagree with the opinion?</li>
                <li><strong>Provide at least three reasons or examples</strong> to support your argument</li>
                <li><strong>Acknowledge complications or counterarguments</strong> ‚Äî show nuanced thinking</li>
                <li><strong>Use advanced punctuation naturally:</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Colons to introduce lists, examples, or explanations</li>
                        <li>Semicolons to connect related ideas or separate complex list items</li>
                        <li>Dashes to add emphasis, interrupt with important info, or set off material with internal punctuation</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
